  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ukraine: Supporting the Judicial Administration Reform</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To support the re-establishment of the High Qualification Commission of Judges (HQCJ). 2) To support vetting of the High Council of Justice (HCJ). 3) To improve internal procedures of the HQCJ and HCJ. 4) To facilitate resumption of merit-based appointment of new judges and unbiased qualification assessment of sitting judges by the HQCJ. 5) To facilitate fair consideration of complaints against sitting judges by the vetted HCJ.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The HQCJ Selection Commission, the HCJ Ethics Council, the new HQCJ and HCJ, the Ukrainian Judiciary and the public at large.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen the efficiency, integrity and accountability of Ukraine&apos;s judicial administration.</narrative>
  </description>
